
[1]bribe

   BRIBE, n.

   1. A price, reward, gift or favor bestowed or promised with a view to
   pervert the judgment, or corrupt the conduct of a judge, witness or
   other person. A bribe is a consideration given or promised to a person,
   to induce him to decide a cause, give testimony, or perform some act
   contrary to what he knows to be truth, justice or rectitude. It is not
   used in a good sense, unless in familiar language.
